Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper deals with temporal action localization in videos, which is a subfield of computer vision. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed marginalized average attentional network (MAAN) is a machine learning model that learns a set of latent discriminative probabilities in an end-to-end fashion. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a novel approach to weakly-supervised learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with video data and proposes a method for temporal action localization, which is a multimedia task. 
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper proposes a method for generating better class activation sequences, which is related to natural language processing and text classification.
